<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - HUBS, BEARINGS, AND SEALS - BEARING CUP (RACE) - INSTALL
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>INSTALL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The bore must be clean of grease and debris. Heat the hub evenly throughout in an oven to
                180&#176;F to 210&#176;F (82&#176;C - 99&#176;C) for approximately 30 minutes.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After the hub is up to temperature, quickly remove it from the oven and place the bearing
                cup into the bore. Carefully tap cup into hub using a criss-cross pattern. Be sure cup is properly
                seated. If the cup does not fit easily into the hub:
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove cup from hub per cup removal procedure.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Reheat the hub.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Refrigerate a NEW cup to -20&#176;F (-29&#176;C).</para>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>Wear gloves when handling hot or cold components to prevent personal injury.</para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Repeat step 2.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To verify that the cup is fully seated and aligned, a 0.002" feeler gauge should
                <emph type="bold">not</emph>
                fit between the cup and bearing backup.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After hub is at room temperature, proceed with normal seal and hub installation.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
